                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/101.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 18, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>332. Your 256, June 10. Enrico Ajello still detained for military service. Inform
                    his brother Antonio, 430 31st Avenue, New York, and request $100 to be
                    telegraphed Embassy to maintain him pending release.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy.</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
